  "The ", TEX ///$a^{th}$///, " Hirzebruch surface is a complete normal toric
  variety.  It can be defined as the ", TEX ///$\PP^1$///, "-bundle over ", 
  TEX ///$X = \PP^1$///, " associated to the sheaf ", 
  TEX ///${\mathcal O}_X(0) \oplus {\mathcal O}_X(a)$///, ".  It is also the 
